{"lemma": "فِي", "slug": "فِي", "root": "ف.#", "root_slug": "ف-_", "root_link": "/words/roots/ف-_", "pos": "PREP", "pos_camel": "prep", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "فِي", "root": "", "pos": "P", "occurrence_count": 1701}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["prep", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 6}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n34892", "n34893"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D9%8A"}}, "translations": {"en": "in", "fa": "در", "ur": "میں", "tr": "içinde", "id": "di dalam", "bn": "মধ্যে", "es": "en", "fr": "dans", "de": "in", "ru": "в", "zh": "在"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "prep", "gloss": "in, within"}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "during, for a duration of"}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "in with, among, together with"}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "of, about, in regards to, pertaining to, in the subject or topic of", "examples": [{"text": "عِنْدِي سُؤَالٌ فِي النَّحْوِ", "english": "I have a question about grammar"}]}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "on account of, for the reason of, in relation to", "examples": [{"text": "عُوقِبْتُ فِي ذَنْبِي", "english": "I was punished for my crime."}]}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "times, multiplied by, to have a measure of this by this", "examples": [{"text": "أَرْبَعَةٌ فِي خَمْسَةٍ يُسَاوِي عِشْرِينَ", "english": "Four times five equals twenty."}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Possibly related to Proto-Semitic *pay- (“mouth, an orifice, an entrance, a means in or to enter”), cognates with Hebrew פֹּה (“here”) and פִּי (“multiplied, -fold”, literally “with, to have this length with this width”) and Ugaritic 𐎔 (p, “here, in this place or in this time; in the manner of, relating or pertaining to”), and Proto-Semitic *piʔat- (“side; border; front, facing part of anything”), i. e. the same word as فِئَة (fiʔa, “troop”), since this word is retained in Ge'ez only in the combination ለፌ (läfe, “in the direction of or from, thence or thither”). It has also functions originally borne by Proto-Semitic *bV-, potentially perceived or originating as a devoiced form of it."}, "ipa": ["/fiː/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n34892", "headword_ar": "فِى", "root": "fY", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "is a particle governing the gen. case [and used in the manners and senses expl in what here follows]. (T, S, M, Mughnee, K.) ―         -b2-  It relates to a receptacle; (Sb, S, M;) and, when used in a wider sense, to that which has some near resemblance thereto; (Sb, M;) [i. e.,] and also to what is considered as a receptacle: (S:) [in other words,] it denotes inclusion, or inbeing, (Msb, Mughnee, K, TA,) either in relation to place or in relation to time: (Mughnee, K, TA;) properly and tropically. (Msb, Mughnee, TA.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gulibati", "text_ar": "غُلِبَتِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@lr~uwmu fiY A^adonaY A@loA^aroDi wahumo mino baEodi galabihimo sayagolibuwna", "text_ar": "ا@لرُّومُ فِى اَدْنَى ا@لْاَرْضِ وَهُمْ مِنْ بَعْدِ غَلَبِهِمْ سَيَغْلِبُونَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY biDoEi siniyna", "text_ar": "فِى بِضْعِ سِنِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The Greeks have been overcome in the nearer,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "nearest, part of the land, and they, after the overcoming of them, shall overcome in some few years"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], in the Kur [xxx. 1 — 3], is an ex. of its relation to place and to time. (Mughnee.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "walakumo fiY A@loqiSaASi Hay`wpN", "text_ar": "وَلَكُمْ فِى ا@لْقِصَاصِ حَيٰوةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And there is, to you, in retaliation, life,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an advantage,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(respecting the meaning of which see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HY", "text_ar": "حى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) in the Kur ii. 175,] is an ex. of its being used tropically, (Mughnee.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adoxalotu AlxaAtama fiY A^uSobaEiY", "text_ar": "اَدْخَلْتُ الخَاتَمَ فِى اُصْبَعِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an ex. of its relation to place, but the proposition is inverted [i. e. the meaning is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I inserted my finger into the signet-ring"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mughnee.) [Using it properly,] you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmaA='u fiY AlA_inaA='i", "text_ar": "المَا=ءُ فِى الاـِنَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The water is in the vessel"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa fiY AljiraAbi", "text_ar": "هُوَ فِى الجِرَابِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It is in the wallet,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Alkiysi", "text_ar": "فِى الكِيسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the purse"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa fiY baToni A^um~ihi", "text_ar": "هُوَ فِى بَطْنِ اُمِّهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He is in the belly of his mother"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa fiY Algul~i", "text_ar": "هُوَ فِى الغُلِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He is in the shackle for the neck"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (M:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayodN fiY Ald~aAri", "text_ar": "زَيْدٌ فِى الدَّارِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Zeyd is in the house"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (S, M, * Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "within the house,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the midst of it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Ald~aAri", "text_ar": "فِى الدَّارِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", means"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAxilihaA", "text_ar": "دَاخِلِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wasoTahaA", "text_ar": "وَسْطَهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (T:) and [using it tropically, you say,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~ak~u fiY Alxabari", "text_ar": "الشَّكُّ فِى الخَبَرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Doubt,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "uncertainty, is in the information"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.) The saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiyhi EayobN", "text_ar": "فِيهِ عَيْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In him is a fault,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "blemish"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], if relating to a real"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eayob", "text_ar": "عَيْب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", is proper; and if relating to an ideal"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eayob", "text_ar": "عَيْب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", tropical: the former is such as the amputation of the hand of the thief, and the redundance of a hand; and the latter, such as the runningaway of a slave. (Msb.) [When relating to time, it may in some cases be rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "during;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY A^ay~aAmK maEoduwdaAtK", "text_ar": "فِى اَيَّامٍ مَعْدُودَاتٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur ii. 139, i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "during,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "certain"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "numbered days."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a A^aSoHaAba A@lojan~api A@loyawoma fiY $ugulK", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ اَصْحَابَ ا@لْجَنَّةِ ا@لْيَوْمَ فِى شُغُلٍ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAkihuwna", "text_ar": "فَاكِهُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur xxxvi. 55, may be rendered (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily the inmates of Paradise this day shall be in the midst of diverting occupation, cheerful,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "happy."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "The phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^am~aA qawoluhu ka*aA fiyhi maA fiyhi", "text_ar": "اَمَّا قَوْلُهُ كَذَا فِيهِ مَا فِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", lit. (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As to his saying thus, in it is what is in it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used as a polite expression of objection, or contradiction; like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiyhi taA^am~ulN", "text_ar": "فِيهِ تَاَمُّلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v. In many instances,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may be rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "concerning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in respect of;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaAla fiyhi ka*aA", "text_ar": "قَالَ فِيهِ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He said of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "concerning, him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, thus;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaAla fiY *ikorihi", "text_ar": "قَالَ فِى ذِكْرِهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ka*aA", "text_ar": "كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He said in mentioning him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, thus,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY waSofihi", "text_ar": "فِى وَصْفِهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in describing him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the like hence, for ex., one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kataba kitaAbFA fiY Eilomi All~ugapi", "text_ar": "كَتَبَ كِتَابًا فِى عِلْمِ اللُّغَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He wrote a book of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "concerning the science of lexicology:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and hence, in the Kur ii. 133,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^at~uHaAj~uwnanaA", "text_ar": "اَتُّحَاجُّونَنَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "فِى ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Do ye argue with us concerning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in respect of, God?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b3-  It also denotes concomitance, (Mughnee, K,) and (K) in this ease (Mughnee) it is syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEa", "text_ar": "مَعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb, Mughnee, K.) Thus in the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaAla A@doxuluwA fiY A^umamK", "text_ar": "قَالَ ا@دْخُلُوا فِى اُمَمٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He shall say, Enter ye with peoples"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Msb, Mughnee, TA,) in the Kur [vii. 36]: (Msb, TA:) or, as some say, the meaning is,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY jamaAEapi A^umamK", "text_ar": "فِى جَمَاعَةِ اُمَمٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the company of peoples"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mughnee.) Thus. too, in the phrase, in the Kur [xlvi. 15],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY A^aSoHaAbi", "text_ar": "فِى اَصْحَابِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljan~api", "text_ar": "الجَنَّةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "With the inmates of Paradise"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Msb, TA.) [Or in these and similar instances,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may be rendered, more agreeably with the primary signification, as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Among."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] In the K, the meaning as denoting concomitance and that which is identical with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEa", "text_ar": "مَعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are made distinct: and it has been said that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "denotes the continuance of concomitance and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEa", "text_ar": "مَعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "denotes its commencement; though this is not invariably the case. (MF, TA.) [Hence it is used to denote a combination of two qualities: as in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TuwlN fiY A@sotiroxaA='K", "text_ar": "طُولٌ فِى ا@سْتِرْخَا=ءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Length together with laxness:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(occurring in the K voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TanabN", "text_ar": "طَنَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sawaAdN fiY HumorapK", "text_ar": "سَوَادٌ فِى حُمْرَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Blackness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "blending"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with redness:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the like. And in like manner it is used to denote the combination of the length and breadth of a thing: as in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tuwluhu Ei$oruwna *iraAEFA fiY valaAvi A^a*oruEK EaroDFA", "text_ar": "طُولُهُ عِشْرُونَ ذِرَاعًا فِى ثَلَاثِ اَذْرُعٍ عَرْضًا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Its length is twenty cubits with"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or as we say"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "three cubits in breadth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in which case the number of square cubits is expressed by the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ei$oruwna fiY valaAvK", "text_ar": "عِشْرُونَ فِى ثَلَاثٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as though meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Twenty"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as a multiplicand"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with three"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as its multiplier; i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "twenty multiplied by three:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Daraba", "text_ar": "ضَرَبَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as signifying “ he multiplied. ”]. ―         -b4-  It also denotes the assigning of a cause. (Msb, Mughnee, K.) Thus in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY A^arobaEiyna $aApN", "text_ar": "فِى اَرْبَعِينَ شَاةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "On account,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "because, of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "completing [the possession of]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "forty sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goats,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[the giving of]"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2467}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[for the poor-rate] is incumbent [on the possessor: or this may be rendered,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the case of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the possession"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of forty, a sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is to be given]. (Msb.) And thus in the saying, [in the Kur xii. 32,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fa*`likun~a A@l~a*iY lumotun~aniY", "text_ar": "فَذٰلِكُنَّ ا@لَّذِى لُمْتُنَّنِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiyhi", "text_ar": "فِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And that is he because of whom ye blamed me"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mughnee.) Thus also in the saying, in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a A@moraA^apF daxalati Aln~aAra fiY hir~apK HabasatohaA", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ ا@مْرَاَةً دَخَلَتِ النَّارَ فِى هِرَّةٍ حَبَسَتْهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily a woman entered the fire"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of Hell"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "because of a she-cat which she confined"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "without food]. (Mughnee.) [And thus in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asolafa fiY ka*aA", "text_ar": "اَسْلَفَ فِى كَذَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He paid in advance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beforehand, for,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on account of, such a thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b5-  It also denotes superiority; (Mughnee, K, TA;) i. e. (TA) it is used in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY", "text_ar": "عَلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T, S, M, Msb, TA.) Thus in the saying, in the Kur [xx. 74],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "walaA^uSal~iban~akumo fiY", "text_ar": "وَلَاُصَلِّبَنَّكُمْ فِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ju*uwEi A@ln~axoli", "text_ar": "جُذُوعِ ا@لنَّخْلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And I will assuredly crucify you upon the trunks of palm-trees"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (T, S, Msb, Mughnee, TA.) And so in the verse of 'Antarah cited voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saroHN", "text_ar": "سَرْحٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T, M, Mughnee, TA.) And Yoo asserts that the Arabs say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nazalotu fiY A^abiyka", "text_ar": "نَزَلْتُ فِى اَبِيكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ealayohi", "text_ar": "عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I alighted,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "descended and stopped,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at the abode of thy father"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.) ―         -b6-  It is also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, S, M, Mughnee, K,) sometimes. (S.) Thus in the saying of Zeyd-el-Kheyl,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "watarokabu yawoma Alr~awoEi fiyhaA fawaArisu\n                      \n                     \n                        baSiyruwna fiY TaEoni AlA^abaAhiri wAlkulaY"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mughnee, TA,) meaning,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biTaEoni AlAbAhr wAlklY", "text_ar": "بِطَعْنِ الاباهر والكلى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And horsemen skilful in piercing the aortas and the kidneys ride in the day of fear therein"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, TA.) And thus in a verse cited by Fr,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^arogabu", "text_ar": "اَرْغَبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is made trans. by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eano", "text_ar": "عَنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "instead of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eano", "text_ar": "عَنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T, TA.) [Thus, also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layosa fiY $aYo'K", "text_ar": "لَيْسَ فِى شَىْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is sometimes used for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layosa bi$aYo'K", "text_ar": "لَيْسَ بِشَىْءٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It is nought;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not of any account"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weight;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: see more in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$yA^", "text_ar": "شيا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b7-  It is also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilaY", "text_ar": "اـِلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Mughnee, K.) Thus in the Kur [xiv. 10],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "farad~uwA", "text_ar": "فَرَدُّوا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ayodiyahumo fiY A^afowaAhhm", "text_ar": "اَيْدِيَهُمْ فِى اَفْوَاههم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And they put their hands to their mouths"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mughnee, TA.) ―         -b8-  It is also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino", "text_ar": "مِنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M, Mughnee, K, TA.) Thus in the Kur [xxvii. 12],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY tisoEi A=yaAtK", "text_ar": "فِى تِسْعِ ا=يَاتٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "among, nine signs"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (M, TA.) And in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xu*o liY", "text_ar": "خُذْ لِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ea$orFA mina AlA_ibili fiyhaA faHolaAni", "text_ar": "عَشْرًا مِنَ الاـِبِلِ فِيهَا فَحْلَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Take thou for me ten of the camels; of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "among, them"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "let there be"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two stallions."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA.) [Thus too in the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "huwa fiY A^aSoli qawomihi", "text_ar": "هُوَ فِى اَصْلِ قَوْمِهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He is of,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "among, the purest in race,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of his people:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the like thereof.] ―         -b9-  It also denotes comparison; and this is when it occurs between a preceding [mention of a] thing excelled and a following [mention of a] thing excelling: as in the saying, [in the Kur ix. 38,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famaA mataAEu A@loHay`wpi A@ld~unoyaA fiY A@loA=xirapi A_il~aA qaliylN", "text_ar": "فَمَا مَتَاعُ ا@لْحَيٰوةِ ا@لدُّنْيَا فِى ا@لْا=خِرَةِ اـِلَّا قَلِيلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "But the enjoyment of the present life, in comparison with that which is to come, is no other than little"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mughnee, K.) ―         -b10-  It is also used for compensation; and this is when it is redundant as a compensation for another ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] which is suppressed: as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Darabotu fiymano ragibota", "text_ar": "ضَرَبْتُ فِيمَنْ رَغِبْتَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Darabotu mano ragibota fiyhi", "text_ar": "ضَرَبْتُ مَنْ رَغِبْتَ فِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I beat,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "struck, him whom thou desiredst"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Mughnee, K:) but this is allowed by Ibn-Málik alone. (Mughnee.) ―         -b11-  And it is used for corroboration: (Mughnee, K:) this is when it is redundant without its being for compensation: and this El-Fárisee allows in a case of necessity in verse; citing as an ex.,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A^anaA A^abuwA saEodK A_i*aA All~ayolu dajaA\n                      \n                     \n                        taxaAlu fiY sawaAdihi yaranodajaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I am Aboo-Saad; when the night becomes dark, thou imagining its blackness to be black leather"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mughnee.) And it is thus used in the saying, in the Kur [xi. 43],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waqaAla A@rokabuwA fiyhaA", "text_ar": "وَقَالَ ا@رْكَبُوا فِيهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@rokabuwhaA", "text_ar": "ا@رْكَبُوهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And he said, Embark ye therein,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the like of which occurs also in xviii. 70 and xxix. 65], (Mughnee, K,) accord. to some. (Mughnee.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as a prefixed noun in the gen. case,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fam", "text_ar": "فَم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY~a", "text_ar": "فِىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famiY", "text_ar": "فَمِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", see voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwhN", "text_ar": "فُوهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fwh", "text_ar": "فوه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["S", "M", "T", "K", "Msb", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n34893", "headword_ar": "فَىَّ", "root": "fY", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "is a word expressive of wonder: they say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA faY~a maA liY A^afoEalu ka*aA", "text_ar": "يَا فَىَّ مَا لِى اَفْعَلُ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O my wonder! What has happened to me that I do thus?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: or it is expressive of regret on account of a thing that is passing away [so that this exclamation may be rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Oh! What has happened to me"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]: Ks says that it is not to be written with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[though it is so written in several of the lexicons in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fyA^", "text_ar": "فيا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faYo'a", "text_ar": "فَىْءَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and that it means"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA EajabiY", "text_ar": "يَا عَجَبِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as first expl. above]: and in like manner one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA faY~a maA", "text_ar": "يَا فَىَّ مَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSoHaAbuka", "text_ar": "اَصْحَابُكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O my wonder! What are thy companions?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what manner of men are thy companions?"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mA", "text_ar": "ما"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "here denoting interrogation respecting qualities, or attributes; as in the Kur xxvi. 22]: and he says that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mA", "text_ar": "ما"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this case occupies the place of a noun in the nom. case. (M, TA.) Ks is also related to have said that some of the Arabs express wonder by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faY~a", "text_ar": "فَىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "haY~a", "text_ar": "هَىَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aYo'a", "text_ar": "شَىْءَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and some add"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA fay~amaA", "text_ar": "يَا فَيَّمَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA hay~amaA", "text_ar": "يَا هَيَّمَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA", "text_ar": "يَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ayoy^amaA", "text_ar": "شَيْيَمَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "How good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beautiful, is this!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the K is faulty here; mentioning only"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA fay~amaA", "text_ar": "يَا فَيَّمَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and explaining it as denoting wonder. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-14", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}